body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?  (Must be openly licensed, completely self-contained so can directly run what you provide. Ideally use test_regress format, see https://veripool.org/guide/latest/contributing.html?highlight=test_regress#reporting-bugs)

```
package s_x_pkg;
class s_x_monitor;      
    virtual s_x_if  x_i_vif[0:5];
    extern task dv_drop_check(input int type_i);
endclass :s_x_monitor
task s_x_monitor::dv_drop_check(input int type_i);
 int hvec_deco;
 fork
  begin
     forever begin
        @(x_i_vif[type_i].mcb);
     end
  end
  begin
   forever begin
    if (x_i_vif[type_i].e_x_t_hv && !x_i_vif[type_i].x_e_h) begin
      hvec_deco = x_i_vif[type_i].reverse_decode(x_i_vif[type_i].e_x_t_f_f,
                                                 x_i_vif[type_i].e_x_t_soh,
                                                 x_i_vif[type_i].e_x_t_hdr);
    end
   end
  end
 join
endtask
endpackage
interface s_x_if (input wire sys_clk, input wire sys_rst_n, input async_sys_rst_n);
   logic            e_x_t_hv;
   logic            x_e_h;
   logic            e_x_t_f_f;
   logic [4:0]      e_x_t_soh;
   logic [(14*32)-1:0]   e_x_t_hdr;
  const string cm = "";
   clocking mcb @(posedge sys_clk);
default input #1step output #0.1ns;
input           sys_clk;
input           sys_rst_n;
input           async_sys_rst_n;
input           e_x_t_hv;
        input           e_x_t_f_f;
        input           e_x_t_soh;
        input           e_x_t_hdr;
        inout           x_e_h;
   endclocking
 function int reverse_decode(bit f_f, bit [4:0] soh, bit [447:0] hdr);
endfunction
endinterface
module tb_top;
endmodule : tb_top
```

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

```
verilator --binary  test.sv 
%Error: test.sv:33:13: Duplicate declaration of member name: ''
                                          : ... note: In instance 'tb_top'
   33 |    clocking mcb @(posedge sys_clk);
      |             ^~~

```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator --binary  test.sv
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

```
Verilator 5.041 devel rev v5.040-216-g5a5c38e47
```

What OS and distribution are you using?

```
Linux 5.14.0-570.37.1.el9_6.x86_64
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

(Please avoid attaching screenshots that show text - you can convert images to text using e.g. https://ocr.space)

